kernel_variant.question:
For every integer $n\ge 1$ list the $2^{\,n}-1$ non-empty subsets  
\[
R_1,R_2,\dots ,R_{\,2^{\,n}-1}\subset\{1,2,\dots ,n\}
\]
in the following order:

* first all subsets that do not contain $n$;  
* next all subsets that do contain $n$ but are different from the singleton $\{n\}$;  
* finally the singleton $\{n\}$ itself.

Define the $(2^{\,n}-1)\times(2^{\,n}-1)$ matrix $B_n=(b_{ij})$ by  
\[
b_{ij}=\begin{cases}
0 &\text{if }R_i\cap R_j=\varnothing,\\[3pt]
(-1)^{|R_i\cap R_j|} &\text{if }R_i\cap R_j\ne\varnothing .
\end{cases}
\]

Find a closed formula for $\displaystyle\det B_n$ for every $n\ge 1$.

